</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="64" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="6.[1447,2655,270,587]" pageId="6" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1448,1798,313,342]" pageId="6" pageNumber="64">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Not assessed on The IUCN Red List. The White-collared Fruit Bat was considered conspecific with the Mindanao Fruit Bat (
<taxonomicName box="[2359,2640,352,381]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Ptenochirus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wetmorer">Ptenochirus wetmorer</taxonomicName>
), which was classified as Vulnerable. The White-collared Fruit Bat is certainly rare, with its distribution naturally fragmented in three disjoint populations (Peninsular 
<collectingCountry name="Malaysia" pageId="6" pageNumber="64">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, Borneo, and Sumatra).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
